Hello again Santhosh,  Just following up on my previous message.  Many businesses focus solely on growing by acquiring new customers, rather than generating more revenue from their existing customers.  This limits profit and growth potential, particularly for companies with a recurring revenue model since they have a leaky bucket of churning customers and are failing to scale expansion revenue from their existing customer base.  Common problems that I see are;  -  Having a ‚Äòone price fits all‚Äô model rather than a segmented approach that offers more value for higher prices based on the customers' complexity of needs  -  Lack of price experimentation and customer research to test willingness to pay  -  Value messaging that fails to convey how your solution is the best fit for your ideal customers in the context of their unique set of problems or pain points  All of the above leads to companies guessing at their pricing, matching competitors, resorting to discounts, and ultimately leaving a ton of money on the table.  If any of this sounds familiar, and you are interested in exploring how you could improve pricing capability within the business, then send me a quick reply and I can share a short video webinar to help get you started.  Kind regards, Ayon

SUBJECT: Senior Product Manager, Germany @ Monotype.
CONTENT: Hi Simon,  Thank you for reaching out and considering my application.   Here is an overview of my experience with Algolia at my current and previous companies:  At Dress-for-Less, I implemented Algolia to refine our e-commerce platform's search capabilities. By leveraging Algolia's AI search APIs, I enhanced the search engine to handle natural language queries effectively, significantly improving search relevancy and user satisfaction. This implementation allowed for a more intuitive search experience, where customers could find products accurately based on varied and complex queries.  During my tenure at Delivery Hero, I focused on optimizing Algolia's configuration to better understand and process customer inputs in their natural language. This not only improved the accuracy of search results but also streamlined the ordering process, thereby enhancing overall user experience and operational efficiency.  I am keen to provide a more detailed discussion of my work with Algolia and its impact in a call.  My notice period is 2 weeks and my salary expectation is 105k EUR. I believe it's inline with your expectations. We can negotiate it at the later stages.  Looking forward to talking to you about this opportunity.  Best regards,  Santhosh Kumar

Hey Rajat,¬†  Overall all your resume looks good. well formatted. I like how you have explained your roles in every company.¬† I have a few comments that you might consider incorporating.¬†  1. Provide more specific details about projects and initiatives: Instead of saying "Developed a new flow for sending coach recommendation notifications," you can provide more context by mentioning the specific features or functionalities you implemented, such as "Developed a new flow for sending coach recommendation notifications, including personalized push notifications and in-app alerts."  2. Quantify the impact of your achievements: Instead of stating "resulting in a 5% increase in user engagement," you can provide more specific numbers to highlight the magnitude of your success, such as "resulting in a 5% increase in user engagement, translating to an additional 10,000 monthly active users."  3. Highlight your role and level of responsibility: Instead of saying "Assisted Product lead and UX lead," you can clarify your specific contributions by mentioning the tasks you undertook or the decisions you made, such as "Collaborated with the Product lead and UX lead to conduct user testing and gather feedback, resulting in a 5-screen reduction in the money mentor feature."  4. Showcase the scale or scope of your work: Instead of stating "Managed 3 content projects/campaigns," you can provide more context by mentioning the size of the projects, such as "Managed 3 large-scale content projects/campaigns with budgets exceeding ‚Ç¨50,000 each."  5. Explain the challenges or obstacles you faced: Instead of simply mentioning "Collaborated with Senior Managers and agencies," you can provide more information about the challenges you encountered or the unique aspects of the collaboration, such as "Collaborated with Senior Managers and external agencies to gain insights into the highly competitive brand landscape, resulting in a comprehensive market analysis report and actionable recommendations.  Thanks, Santhosh.

CONVERSATION TITLE: Lead PM Opportunity - Retail/Supplychain Analytics Scale Up - Series A
SUBJECT: Lead PM Opportunity - Retail/Supplychain Analytics Scale Up - Series A
CONTENT: Procurement   Delivery Hero  At Delivery Hero's Q-Commerce business, I developed a data-driven procurement strategy for 1,500+ small dark stores in 28 countries. Using just-in-time inventory management and machine learning algorithms, I optimized stock levels, reduced waste, and minimized out-of-stock instances from 8% to <2%. My work had a significant impact on improving efficiency, reducing costs, and improving customer satisfaction. Through this project, I gained valuable experience in advanced forecasting, demand planning, and inventory management techniques.  Wayfair    At Wayfair, I developed an inventory platform that enabled direct purchase orders to 1,000+ suppliers, optimized delivery planning to 17 large fulfillment centers across North America, and reduced out-of-stock instances from 15% to <5%. I collaborated closely with the supplier network to streamline the procurement process and establish seamless communication channels. My work had a significant impact on improving operational efficiency, increasing revenue, and enhancing customer satisfaction. Through this project, I gained valuable experience in inventory management, supply chain logistics, and vendor management.

CONVERSATION TITLE: Lead PM Opportunity - Retail/Supplychain Analytics Scale Up - Series A
SUBJECT: Lead PM Opportunity - Retail/Supplychain Analytics Scale Up - Series A
CONTENT: Pricing:   Zalora.com  I helped implement a pricing strategy at Zalora.com that improved margins by 3% across the entire assortment. I conducted a thorough analysis of pricing history and market trends to identify areas for optimization. Using data analysis tools, I collaborated with the pricing team to develop algorithms that could dynamically adjust prices based on real-time market conditions. We implemented these algorithms across the product lines and closely monitored their performance, making adjustments as necessary. The project was successful in achieving the margin improvement target and keeping the company competitive. Through this project, I gained valuable experience in data analysis, algorithm development, and project management.   Alibaba‚Äôs South east Asian Business - Lazada   At Alibaba.com, I worked on a data product that provided insights to large group companies such as Coca-Cola, Samsung, and Apple. By analyzing customer, pricing, and competitive data, I helped these companies improve their revenue by 10% YoY in their Southeast Asian business. Additionally, my work improved the profit margins of Alibaba's Southeast Asian business (Lazada) by 1.5%. Through this project, I gained valuable experience in data analysis and product development. Overall, my work had a significant impact on the performance of both the group companies and Alibaba's Southeast Asian business.

CONVERSATION TITLE: TeamLead Product Analytics - Berlin - Unicorn Startup!
SUBJECT: TeamLead Product Analytics - Berlin - Unicorn Startup!
CONTENT: Hi Santhosh Kumar  A future Unicorn start-up in Berlin with ‚Ç¨100 million+ in funding is looking for a Product Analytics Team Lead.  In this role you will be working with data in several cross-functional (mission) teams. You will be responsible for growing and developing your team as well as enabling the mission team to take action based on data. You will help to measure the impact of their new product features and create a culture of data informed decision making. You will work in a cross-functional team building products from scratch and you will also be responsible for future hiring plans.  The Role: - Manage team of 2-4 data analysts - mentor and motivate, responsible for recruiting and growing the team - Responsible for routines for reactive and proactive request gathering & prioritization - Influence product decisions by providing actionable insights based on deep dives into customer behaviors - Drive product experimentation by defining objectives, testing techniques, ensuring right tracking, analyzing the results and providing clear recommendations - Take an active role in data democratization by implementing metrics, building dashboards, and up-skilling your stakeholders - Establish best practice for data analysis, code reviews and story telling in your team - Collaborate with different teams such as Product, BI, Data platform  - Promote data insight and usage in the organization  Profile:  - 1-2 years managerial experience including hiring, mentoring & growing a team. - Hands-on experience with A/B testing and product analytics - Strong SQL skills and basic Python for data analysis (e.g. pandas, scikit-learn) - Data visualization and reporting tools (e.g. Looker, Tableau, Jupyter Notebooks) - Ability to work with stakeholders across all levels  Please let me know if you are interested in hearing more details about the role.  Best  Kit Pelham Principal Consultant at Xcede

SUBJECT: Product Manager
CONTENT: Hi Santhosh Kumar,  My name is Michelle and I am a Recruiter with Altera Staffing. Our client operating in stealth mode is running a confidential search for a Product Manager to join their remote team.  They‚Äôre building a digital campus that fits in your pocket. As a population, students have specific demands: they need to chat with formal and informal groups, learn about events around campus, and share content that's only relevant within on-campus circles. Until now, there hasn't been a single app where they could do all these things. Their platform combines the organization of Discord, the audio rooms of Clubhouse, the rapid-fire content of TikTok, and the personalized content feeds of Twitter. It's currently in early UX research but will scale massively over time. Expect talented, motivated co-workers from around the world, all united by a performance-driven, egalitarian Silicon Valley mindset.   As a Product Manager, you‚Äôll lead a new product initiative within an emerging space. Your clear vision is informed by expertise in the field, but you aren't content to rest on your laurels. You are always developing your own skillset and making your team better. Communication and relationship-building guide you, whether with stakeholders, team members, or customers. You have a comprehensive view of market forces and respond with innovative solutions. The ideal candidate has several years of product management experience and an entrepreneurial mindset. CONVERSATION TITLE: Senior Product Manager - Market leading classifieds platform - Dubai
SUBJECT: Senior Product Manager - Market leading classifieds platform - Dubai
CONTENT: Hi Santhosh Kumar,  Salt are currently representing one of our key clients, a major digital classifieds platform based in Dubai who have instructed us on a global search for a highly talented Senior Product Manager to join their expanding team. To give you an idea of scale, the platform boats over 15 million page views per month, and is the market leader in their sector across Dubai and the wider the Middle East.   Our client is looking to identify a very high calibre Senior Product Manager with an excellent understanding of product development processes and launching new products, with a background working for a successful digital or ecommerce platform, hence my interest in your profile.  The Senior Product Manager will be responsible for defining, validating, communicating, and delivering end-to-end products that solves the most important and complex problems for their users and customers, defining Product strategy and sitting in the intersection of Technology, Business, and Design to determine what is best for their users, customers, and company.  The Senior Product Manager role is a permanent position, to be based from their Dubai HQ. The package includes a market leading (tax free) salary together with a range of benefits and relocation scheme. To give you some benchmarks on the cost of living here in Dubai, you may or may not be aware that the cost of living in Dubai is approx. 35% less than London, 25% less than Sydney ‚Äì this, combined with the very attractive income tax-free salary is one of the many factors that are fuelling the ever-increasing drive of expats relocating to the UAE.   If you are interested in discussing the opportunity with me in more detail, I‚Äôd be interested to talk to you ASAP. If so, please can you send me a copy of your CV and/or contact number so I can reach you to discuss.  Kind regards, Tom  Tom Turpin Director - Technology  +971 524 300 844 tturpin@welovesalt.com

SUBJECT: Regards - Reaching out - Sr Mgr Digital Products, CX role with leading Retail firm, based in Dubai
CONTENT: Hello Santosh,  Greetings. Kindly pardon this unsolicited msg. I Head the Dubai office of a global US based search firm - MRI Network. The firm's legacy dates back to 1965 and currently has more than 250 offices worldwide. The Dubai office has been around since 2001 and this is my 8th year with the firm.  MRI Network has been ranked in the top 20 out of 250 US based search firms for 2017, 2018 and 2019 by Forbes.  While my intention is not to disturb you in your current role however, I wish to speak on a key mandate with one of our marquee clients in Dubai. They are perhaps one of the top 5 well known local names in the UAE and the region. They have more than 25k employees, roughly USD 7bn in Revenues and are specialists on the Retail side. They have built and own some of the most well known malls in the UAE and the region. Their business interests extend from retail, malls, entertainment, hospitality (hotels), real estate among others. They own the exclusive rights to the Carrefour brand in this part of the world.  Within Retail, Carrefour is a prominent segment (which is a top 10 'popular brand' in the UAE). SUBJECT: Senior Product Manager @Jimdo - remote possible
CONTENT: Dear Santhosh Kumar,  My name is Chung, I‚Äôm Tech Recruiter at Jimdo. Nice to e-meet you :) I think your profile looks very interesting, at least on paper you check a lot of boxes.  Your profile caught my attention because of impressive career path and your remarkable experience at Delivery Hero or Alibaba!  To give you a bit context, Jimdo‚Äôs mission is to unleash the power of small businesses and help them thrive by providing a platform with easy to use tools to accompany their business and success. Since the beginning of 2020 Jimdo, and especially our product and engineering organization, goes through a strong growth period. Right now, we have 13 cross-functional team and due to our ambitious plans for more customer products and features, more teams will be created and existing teams will be level up. In total we have 250 employees and counting.   We are looking for Senior Product Mangers who are able to raise the bar for the whole team. We expect you to define compelling strategies and roadmaps for the most impactful product teams in our organisation. You will work very close together with other Product- and Engineering Managers, as well as with other stakeholders from business, design, data, engineering, and of course our customers. We won't limit you in any way to drive customer centric initiatives, wether its within your team or across our organisation. We see pro-activeness as a virtue and if you are also in favour of data-driven decisions, then sky is the limit for you at Jimdo!  Btw we love remote. While we support anyone who‚Äôd like to relocate to Hamburg you can also stay and work from wherever you are :)  Feel free to check our socials and if this all sounds interesting for you, I‚Äôd be super happy to have a first chat with you.  https://twitter.com/jimdo https://instagram.com/jimdo_official/ https://www.jimdo.com/  Looking forward to your response!  Chung Huynh Technical Recruiter at Jimdo (he/him)

CONTENT: Hi Santhosh Kumar üëã ‚Ä® I hope you don't mind me getting in touch with you, however I wanted to check if you would be open to having a conversation about joining us at Revolut?   Here at Revolut we are looking for Product Owners at all different levels to join our rocket ship at either our London office/ working remotely. Your experience looks really interesting, so I was hoping to tell you a bit more about our future plans.  Our mission is to become the No.1 mobile banking app that everyone around the world can use in a safe and secure way. After 5 years we have over 12 million customers using our product and those numbers are growing significantly day by day. We have over 2000 employees doing great work in offices around the world. We have launched in 35+ countries and due to several rounds of funding we are one of the fastest growing FinTech companies in the EU. ü¶Ñ ‚Ä® We‚Äôre looking for Product Owners to join us within our retail, business, payments, fincrime and internal product teams. You will own your product area globally end-to-end, identify market opportunities and define your product's vision and strategy. You will be responsible for a dedicated product team of talented developers, designers and data scientists who's work will make a difference to millions of people across the world!  The teams have a lot they want to achieve, so it would be a really exciting time for you to join us and get involved in some really interesting projects! üß†  If you would be open to hearing more, then I would love to schedule a call with you so I can take you through everything in much more detail. CONTENT: Dear Santhosh Kumar,   Hope all is well. Hi Santhosh,  How are you? My name is Flor and the reason for my message is that at Chalhoub Group (http://www.chalhoubgroup.com/) we are looking for an experienced Product Manager to join our Dubai based Digital Hub team that is handling the digital transformation process of our Fashion & Accessories brands (over 30).   The team is an international team and the role involves relocation to UAE so the company offers relocation assistance, as well as a comprehensive relocation package.  The Product Manager will be responsible for defining and delivering key product features and improvements for the ecommerce of several luxury brands. Please find attached the JD for the role.  Some of the interesting challenges this position will offer are: Chalhoub is undergoing a massive digital transformation and the Fashion and Accessories Digital Hub acts as a startup within a large and established group so opportunities are big. This person will be working for several ecommerce sites, not just one, and a wide variety of technologies.  The person will be working within an agile environment and an international team made up of people from different nationalities.  The Chalhoub Group services luxury brands in the Middle East and they are currently undergoing a digital transformation to compete with major retailers in the market so Digital Hub is a business unit that has been created to lead this digital transformation for the fashion and accessories verticals in the company.   Nowadays there are 33 brands in the Fashion vertical that need to be online since only 15 of them are online right now so the main challenge will be to digitalize the brands, both by creating multi brand websites for small brands or ecommerce sites for the bigger ones and that way support the group's growth at an online level. Some of the high end brands under the umbrella of Chalhoub are Louis Vuitton, Lacoste, Swarovski, Dior, Celine, Lanvin, Swarovski, Lacoste and Carolina Herrera and the company also has its concept brands such as Level Shoes, Tanagro and Tryano.  The company offers competitive salaries and a comprehensive benefits package, including medical and life insurance, performance based bonus, 23 annual leaves, flight tickets to your home country and relocation package if needed. And please note that there is NO income tax in UAE so salaries are almost net salaries.  Please let me know if you can be interested and I will tell you the next steps.  Cheers,  Flor

SUBJECT: PI - Job Opportunity
CONTENT: Dear Santhosh Kumar,   I hope you‚Äôre well, this is Dena from Prime Insight. Are you open to new opportunities? I have a new AVP, E-commerce role at Wing Tai in SG where they are developing a B2B digital market place for all brands, not only Wing Tai brands and products. Wing Tai are a listed and leading regional property and lifestyle company.  Reporting to the Head of E-commerce, they are looking for an AVP of E-Commerce to lead the team in creating a successful, sustainable and scale-able E-Comm business from conception through to implementation. Working closely with the tech product team, you would create an E-Comm platform that enables selling on website, app and 3rd party channels domestically or cross border. You would work with the Analytics team to monitor traffic and data to continuously improve and create a smooth experience. They would first focus on products (supplies for the property industry such as cement, piping, machinery, etc) and then look at services (such as contractors and specialists.)  You would need a degree and a min of 5 yr‚Äôs work experience with 3 yrs of relevant experience in e-commerce and e-tailing / online supply chain management. Solid ability to work in a matrix environment with strong communication and interpersonal skills, ability to lead and motivate a team, good e-commerce with merchandising experience a plus, and a proactive and results-driven attitude.  This is a huge venture for Wing Tai and they are investing a lot into this initiative, the CTO comes from eBay and hired all the new Heads and this person will be the manager focused on E-Comm to oversee and execute with their team based on the Head‚Äôs strategies. Pay could be in the SGD 8-10K x 12 months + bonus region. If interested, please send your CV and current and expected salary and notice period to dharon@primeinsight.com or share any relevant referrals. Thank you!  Best regards,  Dena   Dena Haron Associate Director at Prime Insight - Digital and Marketing Recruitment Specialist

SUBJECT: Job Opportunity - Head of Data Science (FMCG & Retail)
CONTENT: Hi Santhosh Kumar,   I hope you are well.   I am wondering if you'd be interested in hearing about a very exciting opportunity with a rapidly growing start-up in Singapore that operates across the retail and FMCG industries.   The organisation has developed a product that is used internally to develop insights from data from retailers. These insights are then delivered to brands and this organisation works with those brands and data to strategize campaigns and initiatives to help optimise their revenue from retailers.   They are currently looking for an experienced candidate to head their data science team. This role will involve regular statistical modelling and implementation of data science techniques. You will also be working closely with their account management and tech team to ensure that you are providing the data-driven insights to help them secure ROI from their clients.   You will also be developing machine learning and data science products/features to enhance their services offerings to clients.   I would be very happy to discuss this role in more depth over the phone. If you are keen, please send me your CV in advance to ddelacruz@primeinsight.com so we can speak in depth. Thanks! SUBJECT: RE: Your application to Ignite Talent Asia: Next steps
CONTENT: Hi Felice, yes. I am good in optimization/ Simulation modelling. However, I am not sure of your client's expectations. There are several techniques of modelling/ simulation available in the market. It can start from basic modelling in Excel solver to complicated machine learning techniques based on several degrees of mathematical equations. I have worked on modelling and I have simulated those models in my work experience.¬† If your client insist extensive experience in modelling/simulation, may be I can prepare a sample model for one of their problems. Well known companies like uber give large datasets to potential candidates to solve them before starting interviews.

SUBJECT: RE: Your application to Ignite Talent Asia: Next steps
CONTENT: Thanks for the detailed reply. For optimisation/simulation modelling would you say you are very experienced here? The client wont consider applications who lack this, so I would like to be clear here :)

SUBJECT: RE: Your application to Ignite Talent Asia: Next steps
CONTENT: 1)	Strong communication skills (able to explain technical concepts to non technical audience) -   I believe that I have strong communication skills. For instance, when I was working as a Product Manager to develop certain Logistics and warehousing related features for Zalora, I had good experience is dealing with people of various skill sets and technical understanding. I have worked with various types of users to learn about functional requirements and technical needs to deliver solutions.   2)	Strong knowledge in supply chain concepts ‚Äì   Over the past few years, I have worked on building and automating several sections of supply chains in Redmart and Zalora. In Redmart, I worked on developing a tool to forecast demand, generate daily order quantities and align with supply availabilities. In Zalora, I designed market place order management flow for Malaysia and Singapore and automated it through an internally developed tool called seller center. Further, I have a Master‚Äôs Degree in supply chain from National University of Singapore. I have a good understanding of various supply chain concepts through my past and current work experience and education.   3)	Data ETL skills ‚Äì SQL ‚Äì  I use SQL on day to day basis to Extract, Transform and Learn data. In Zalora , I have worked on relational data bases built using Amazon Redshift. I use SQL not only for ad hoc analysis but also for establishing connections between programs written using R to analyse large scale data.   4)	Solid modelling skills - building simulation/optimization models ‚Äì Following are the models which I built during my work experience  ‚Ä¢	Redmart ‚Äì I have built a model to recommend daily order quantities for replenishing stocks. First the model forecasts the demand using past history of sales, seasonality and forward plan. Then, it calculates the order quantities based on supply availability, warehouse space availability and safety stock requirements. The forecasting part is the most complex as it involves working on huge past sales history time series data sets.  I modelled forecasting using a concept called ARIMA in programming language R.  ‚Ä¢	Zalora ‚Äì I designed the model for logistics network to fulfil market place orders in Malaysia and Singapore. This involved building a model to optimize distance travelled by the 3PL vehicles and increase efficiency. I built this model using a concept called Monte Carlo simulation, which is based on normal distribution. ‚Ä¢	Larsen & Toubro Limited -  I worked on building optimization models to distribute inventory across the supply chain where the company is located across various parts of India.

SUBJECT: Career Opportunity in Planning
CONTENT: Dear Santhosh Kumar Setty,   I hope this message finds you in good spirits. This is Gildo from en world in Singapore.   The reason for my contact today is because one of my clients, a global FMCG company with over 26,000 employees across the world and world-renowned brands in more than 120 countries, is currently searching for an experienced Planning Executive and I believe your background is very relevant for their requirements.  Please see below the general description and minimal requirements for this role:  Summary of role  ‚Ä¢	Finished Goods (FGs) inventory planning including forecasting and replenishment of FGs shipment.  ‚Ä¢	Liaise closely with Brand, Trade Marketing, Asia Customer Service and Factory Planning teams for new launches planning and shipments.   Main Area of Responsibilities:  ‚Ä¢	Liaise with Asia Customer Service and factory planning team on monthly import orders via SNP file. Manages the intercompany logistics to ensure timely and proper product importation and documentation. Taking new launches, new packaging, etc into consideration when planning ‚Ä¢	Monthly rolling sales forecast (Webtool) and ending inventory (SPFG) uploading into a Global Platform. ‚Ä¢	Manage destruction process for duty unpaid stocks and PQF (Product Quality Feedback) process and trade returns. Monitor and manage NTMs write off closely with factory. ‚Ä¢	Support for material master creation via SAP whenever needed. ‚Ä¢	Provide backup for Sales Operations Support Manager & Sales Admin Associates whenever needed.  If you feel this could be interesting for your career, I will be happy to give you all the details over the phone or face to face. If you have any questions, feel free to contact me at any time. All my contact details are below my signature.  I am looking forward to hearing from you soon. Best regards   Gildo Aleshinsky Director en world Singapore Pte Ltd  Direct: +65 6420 0578 | Mobile: +65 9646 1522 Email: gildo.a@enworld.com

Dear Santhosh,  Thanks for accepting my invite.  We are actively looking to fill the below role, in case you or your friends are interested, please do send a copy of the updated CV at the earliest.   Title: Devices Demand Planner - Accessory Reports to: Asia Demand Planning Lead Location: Singapore, Alexandra Technopark   Job Description  In support of the ‚ÄòOne Microsoft‚Äô strategy which is focused on creating a family of devices and services that empower people around the globe at home, at work and on the go, for the activities they value most, we have recently established a SMSG Demand Planning function in the Operations organization. The SMSG Devices Demand Planner co-ordinates cross-functional efforts to ensure the availability of Microsoft Devices to the right place at the right time and the productivity of inventory across MS commercial and consumer channels across all the assigned markets.   We are looking for candidates with experience in demand planning and business transformation. This role will manage the end-to-end Demand signal process for Asia‚Äôs device accessories. This position will primarily engage with regional and global Demand Planning team, Supply chain functions and Subsidiary Sales team as appropriate to ensure Asia‚Äôs accessories Demand signal is captured, refined and accurately reflected in the demand planning systems. This position will report to the Regional leader for Demand Planning.    Success in this position requires proven business results in a Sales & Operations Planning environment, a passion for operational excellence, quality, process improvements, communication, cross-group collaboration skills and a desire to make an impact. The ideal candidate has a passion for Sales & Operations Processes, has a strong analytical skill set, is agile and possesses mature organizational abilities and ability to deal with ambiguity.   Key Responsibilities: ÔÇß	Asia Demand planning: Coordinate the consolidation, validation, refinement of the Accessory demand signal across segments. Manage the submission of the Demand signal across segments and territories. Identify key Demand signal trends, provide business insight and coordinate recommendations and actions. ÔÇß	Demand Plan of Record Management: Monitor variances vs. Demand plan of record through proactive performance management. Lead and influence stakeholders on managing exceptions. Engage with Supply team to identify any impact to supportable demand and partner with Channel Operations Managers to communicate actions plans to the Field to address gaps.  ÔÇß	Apply product roadmap (NPI/EOL), price/promo assumptions to country and area demand plans. Leverage demand/supply recon and sell down plans (EOL) to shape the regional demand signal for Accessory. ÔÇß	Process Management: Continuously improve demand signal process. Document and define end-to-end process improvement across functions, systems and stakeholders. Engage with capability teams to ensure alignment in short and long term demand planning system/tool roadmaps. ÔÇß	Cross Group Collaboration & Stakeholder Management: Develop and maintain productive relationships with Sales & Operations, Supply Chain, Marketing and Segment teams.   Qualifications/Experience: ÔÇß	5+ years‚Äô experience in demand planning, forecasting or Sales & Operations related functions (required) ÔÇß	Leadership of cross functional projects including setting scope, reaching consensus, execution, and presenting results. ÔÇß	Experience in delivering results across functions and geographies within a matrix environment.  ÔÇß	Experience in demand planning across segments (B2B, B2C & Direct) is a plus. ÔÇß	Experience with MS Office Applications, including advanced knowledge of Excel and PowerPoint.  ÔÇß	Experience with SAP a plus   Personal Attributes ÔÇß	Possess business acumen, able to think and plan strategically, and also able to execute tasks with strong attention to detail.  ÔÇß	Strong communication, interpersonal & presentational skills with proven impact & influence to senior stakeholders within a subsidiary/regional environment.  ÔÇß	Results orientated with strong analytical and problem resolution skills ÔÇß	Ability to be resourceful and work effectively while operating in a lean matrix organization within a country or regional context ÔÇß	Ability to work under continual deadline constraints ÔÇß	Strong process/system background and proven capability to rapidly understand, use and drive improvements in new processes/systems ÔÇß	Strong critical thinking and ability to drive resolution in ambiguous situations  Education: ‚Ä¢	Bachelors degree in business, supply chain, operations management, or engineering. This description has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed by employees within this position.  The actual duties, responsibilities, and qualifications may vary based on assignment or group.  Look forward to hear from you.  Kind Regards Deepika a-degul@Microsoft.com

Dear Santhosh Kumar,


As the UK has now left the EU single market and customs union, I wanted to highlight some actions to take if you run an EU-based business which trades with the UK.


1. For the movement of goods between the EU and UK: Check import and export procedures with your country‚Äôs customs authority and follow the necessary border requirements to ensure goods are not stopped at the border. Talk to trading partners in the UK to agree responsibilities and check you have the correct paperwork for goods you trade.


2. For EU hauliers transporting goods: There are new rules for drivers, vehicles and goods. Talk to your haulage firm to check that paperwork requirements are fulfilled, including submitting an entry summary declaration if needed. 


3. Additional requirements for trading some products: There are new rules for trading agri-food, animal, plant and fish products. Businesses importing controlled goods from the UK also require a licence from the relevant licensing authority. Find out more here.


4. If you sell to UK customers: You may need to take additional actions if you are placing manufactured goods on the market in Great Britain or Northern Ireland, and review product marking, labelling and packaging. There are new rules for paying VAT on goods sold directly to UK customers or via an online market place. 


5. When travelling to the UK for business: Check if you need a visa before travelling. There are specific requirements relating to COVID-19. This includes providing a passenger locator form, proof of a coronavirus negative test and self-isolating on arrival. There are different rules and penalties if travelling to England, Scotland, Wales or Northern Ireland.


6. Use the Trade with the UK tool: for information on taxes, tariffs, commodity codes and regulations. It also provides information for goods going into Northern Ireland.


Check. Take Action. Keep your business with the UK moving.

Making sure our energy systems meet growing global demand is critical. Ensuring these energy systems are developed in long-term, sustainable way is the priority of many stakeholders, both in the public and private sectors.UCL’s MSc in Sustainable Energy Systems is a joint programme offered by UCL (ranked #10 in the world) and the University of South Australia (UniSA) and will prepare you for a range of careers that will help ensure the creation of sustainable energy sources.For this 18-month Master's degree, the first four modules take place in London and provide the background to energy systems, how we produce it, how we use it, how much is produced and where, what are the geopolitical implications, and how is this controlled and regulated. Two further modules in London prepare the students for undertaking research and introduces them to both qualitative and quantitative methods, modelling and statistical analysis and presentation skills.Students then go to Adelaide to look in more detail at some of the more practical aspects of energy production; how do the economics work, how do we finance and build energy systems, and how do we maintain the social license to operate necessary for long-term exploitation of the natural resources needed. During this period, students also learn about low carbon technologies, renewable energy systems and conservation. A fund of AUD $3400 per student will be available to assist with this cost.Finally, the students undertake a six-month industry focussed project in the field of energy systems, making use of the knowledge and understanding they have acquired during the first year.The content will be refreshed annually to reflect the current and global challenges faced in providing affordable, reliable and sustainable energy, today and for future generations.To learn more, please visit https://www.ucl.ac.uk/chemeng/prospective-students/postgraduate-taught/msc-sustainable-energy-systems or contact Dr Ady James, at a.james@ucl.ac.uk
